## Summary of Test Results

**Visual Bugs Observed:**
1. **Missing Toolbar**: The Drawnix toolbar/toolbox is completely absent from the interface. There are no visible tool selection buttons (select, text, pen, shape, etc.) anywhere on the screen - not at top, left, right, or bottom.
2. The "默认" (Default) dropdown is visible at the bottom-right but appears to be a page/board selector only.

**Functional Test Results:**
- Double-clicking on blank canvas areas **does NOT create text elements**
- Multiple attempts at different positions (400,150), (400,550), (640,620), (200,600) - all failed to create text elements
- No text input box appeared, no cursor, no text editing mode was triggered
- The double-click on blank canvas feature is **NOT working**

The absence of the toolbar is likely the root cause - the application might be in a "view-only" or "broken" state because the toolbar didn't render properly.

**Conclusion**: The feature "double-click on blank area to add text element" is **NOT functioning**. The text input box does NOT automatically get focus, no cursor appears, and you cannot start typing after double-clicking on blank canvas area. This appears to be caused by the toolbar missing from the interface (a rendering bug), which may have put the canvas in an inactive/broken state for editing.

